<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="I" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Idol" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Idol,</orth> 1) an image worshipped as God, a false God: <cit><quote>well-painted i., image dull and dead,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 212" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 212</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. son 105.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 105, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.2.129" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. IV, 2, 129</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.399" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 4, 399</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.1.257" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 1, 257</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.1.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 1, 7</bibl>.<lb />2) a person worshipped to adoration: <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.4.144" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 4, 144</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 2.3.199" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 3, 199</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.109" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 2, 109</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>